    "created_at": "2015-09-25T09:45:17Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-25T09:45:17Z",
    "body": "It seems that setting titlebar style is a one-way operation, once the window is set to hide the titlebar it becomes impossible to bring it back, I have pushed a commit in [hidden-inset-fullscreen branch](https://github.com/atom/electron/tree/hidden-inset-fullscreen) to show it.\n\nTo very it we can just create a NSWindow with titlebar hidden and then immediately call this:\n\n``` objc-c\nNSUInteger styleMask = [window_ styleMask];\nstyleMask &= !NSFullSizeContentViewWindowMask;\nstyleMask &= !NSUnifiedTitleAndToolbarWindowMask;\n[window_ setStyleMask:styleMask];\n```\n\nInstead of reverting to a normal window, the window just became a frameless window with titlebar completely removed.\n"
  },
